.NEUTRON FLUX WAS MONITORED WITH A SCINTILLATION

IS BASED ON THE PHASE SHIFT FORMALISM.

THE NORMALIZATION OF THE TWO COUNTS - SAMPLE IN AND
SAMPLE OUT - WAS PERFORMED BY INTEGRATING THE PROTON
BEAM CURRENT.
DISAGREEMENT WITH THE THEORETICAL CURVE CALCULATED
FROM THE PHASE SHIFTS AROUND 2.83 MEV, CONFIRMS THE
RESULT BY KFK GROUP, CIERJACKS ET AL., NEUTRON CROSS
SECTIONS AND TECHNOLOGY, NBS SPEC.PUB.299(1968)P.743.

AND FOR DEAD TIME OF ELECTRONICS (0.5 PERC.).

STATISTICAL ERROR BETWEEN 0.8 AND 1.5 PERCENT.
